column2: Personal visit.  Cut weeds today and there was 2.25" of rain yesterday.
Cloudy- very windy- 3" rain last few days.
1" rain- partly cloudy- hot and muggy.
1.3" rain- lots of wind- partly cloudy- 68 F.
75 F partly sunny- no rain last week.
Cold weather- temperature down to 40 degrees F.
Heavy rain past two weeks.  This is the last sample for the year.
Ice on 11/10/86- ice off 4/1/87. Windy- 2.5" rain in last week.
Sunny- breezy- 1.4" rain 2 days ago- pollen is making water green.
Clear- mild east wind- slight algae- warm day.
Slight algae- weeds starting to surface.
Lot more weeds this year- weed cutting progressing well.
Weed cutting almost completed- hot/clear- water clear.
Hot- humid- clear- still cutting weeds.
Opinion effected by weeds- hot- lots of weeds need continuous scuffing.
Still cutting weeds- 3" rain- lots of runoff.
Some weeds still to cut- hot- humid- water cloudy.  Water level: up 2"
Weeds keep growing- will keep cutting.
Lots of weeds- need to start cutting.
No algae- more weeds- started cutting.
Cutting weeds 3-4 days a week.- worse than last year- thinking of poisoning.
Still cutting weeds every day- can't keep up- very disappointing.
Clear- cool- can't keep up with weeds.
Clear and bright- still cutting weeds- lake in awful shape.
Cloudy- cutting weeds 4 days a week since June 1st- lousy lake conditions.
Still cutting weeds- starting to get green slime.
Still weed problems- getting more green- algae slime.
Silt coming into lake- decided to spray weeds around shore.
Lake sprayed- weed cutting starting- too much silt.
Lots of green slime- lake sprayed with diquat.
Sprayed shoreline again- more green slime.
Sprayed with diquat- weeds breaking up- clarity poor- new type weed growth- lots of slime.
Green slime in lake- clarity lousy- "I think they killed too many weeds."
Diquat for weeds- copper sulfate for algae- lake bottom like green mountains- Maybe should just cut weeds
Lake clearing some- bottom still like green mtns.- hope we didn't harm the fish.
Still cutting weeds- green grass type weeds are more abundant.
Cutting weeds- grass like weeds appearing.
Grassy weeds flourishing- still cutting weeds.
Weeds are here again- lots of cutting for another year.
Lots of weeds- mower broke down.
Terrible weed problem- we'll be cutting soon.
Weed cutter broke- lots of weeds.
Cutter still broke- lots of weeds.
Weeds will be poisoned around the 10th of June.
Poisoning was effective- weed growth at minimum because of temp and sun.
Lake color from water let in by ditch that was dug to drain a swamp- silt.
Swamp ditch still staining water- silt.
Getting drainage from 400 acres of swamp + woods because of ditch that was dug- in future 10" of drainage from 600 acre Silver + Iaogami lakes.
Drainage from Silver- Iaogami- and swamps is ruining our lake- this is a lousy situation.
Last year I could see 15' on May 3- 1993.
Last year I could see 16' on 5-21-93.
Weeds are growing + growing + growing + growing.
Weeds are growing + growing + growing + growing.
Cutting weeds again- a- algae bad- will poison soon.
Cutting weeds again.  Algae bad- will poison soon.
Too many weeds.  Lots of algae.  Lake looks lousy.
Too many weeds.  Lots of algae.  Lake looks lousy.

Diversion from Silver/Irogami Lakes is continuing- weed treatment and harvesting continuing- water quality looks fairly good- normal rain- Dennis Weisensel- Dan Helsel and Scott Szymanski on the lake today.
Way too much algae.  Lake looks bad.
Whole bottom of lake covered with algae.  Wish they would stop poisoning lake.

Beautiful day- some floating algae- bottom plants in reasonably good control- desirable plants on the increase- milfoil pretty well controlled with harvesting- water diversion still flowing from Silver/Irogami Lakes through Lake Alpine.

Overcast- windy (15-20mph) - temperature is 50 degrees- no floating algae- plants are dying down- water diversion (Department of Natural Resources permit) from Irogami and Silver Lakes barely flowing through Lake Alpine
Public perception due to coldness.  Run off from marsh is clouding lake- "Irogami".

Beautiful sunny day - temp is 80 degrees - very little floating algae  - underwater plants are healthy/ not a major problem- lake district treating for floating algae/harvesting underwater plants at 3' level (below surface).
Beautiful sunny day- temp is 57 degrees.  Wind is SW @ 10 mph- light and heavy rain in the last several days.  No floating algae- water is very clear.
66 degrees- mostly sunny- water is somewhat choppy- 2 fishermen- 6 mallards.
This is the deepest I've ever measured. I am sure if the lake were deeper- I would have reached 20 feet.
This is my 100 secchi disk reading!
Lake was windy- boat drifted- measurements may not be very accurate.
Sunny and clear light breeze.  84 degrees.
Sunny and clear.  Light breeze.  68 degrees.
Cloudy. 50 F.  Slight breeze- light rain during night- one crane flew over.
Clear.  88 F.  Slight breeze- humid- milkweeds everywhere.
Partly cloudy.  A little breeze.  Lots of birds singing.  85 F.
Clear. 53 F. Breezy. 8 Canadian geese swimming nearby.
Clear- hazy clouds in distance- 45 degrees F with a light breeze.
Clear- slight breeze- 78 degrees. F- spotted one heron and 2 seagulls.
Sunny- clear- 75 degrees. F- flock of 9 geese on lake.
Partly cloudy- 78 deg F. Slight breeze. Saw 1 muskrat- 2 turtles- and 5 seagulls
74 deg F. Clear- no breeze. Saw 1 heron.
Partly sunny- 46 F- mild breeze. Disturbed 6 teal ducks on lake
Partly sunny- 80 F- small breeze. 2 mallards swimming nearby. 2 sandhill cranes flew overhead.
Clear- 88 F- breezy. Lots of kids fishing along shore at Alpine Park
Cloudy- 50 degrees- small breeze- Saw 6 mallards swimming.
Clear and sunny. Opening day of bass fishing- 16

column1: greater than  people fishing on shore at alpine park. Lots of boats out.

column2: Overcast and breezy- 79 degrees. Lake very murky.
Clear and sunny with light breeze- 82 degrees.
Windy with 80% cloud cover- 47 degrees. Lake seems to

column1: greater than  be rather weedy in spots.

column2: 80 F- partly cloudy.  Slight breeze.  Saw 3 turtles- 1 muskrat and 1 fishing boat.
80 F.  Hazy clouds- small breeze.  9 turtles- 1 muskrat and 1 fishing boat.
Temp. 70 F- clear.  Slight breeze.  Algae on the lake.  Water color green-brown.
clear- sunny- 68F- one goose on lake
Partly cloudy- one fisherman in boat- saw one muskrat
70 F- sunny and windy making boat drift.  Geese on lake and pine dust on surface.
90 F.  Sunny.  Geese on lake.  Did D.O. with vials.
weather was warm with a slight breeze and a few clouds No wild life noted on the lake this morning.
Warm-  Lake has a lot of algae and scum floating. no wild life seen on lake or shore
Beautiful day- blur skies a few white clouds.  Eight geese on lake
Beautiful sunny day ith vry light breeze.   Temp 73 degrees

column1: Two sand cranes flew overhead- no wild life on the lake

column2: Beautiful sunny day- a family of five geese on the lake.

column1: The lake doesn't look to good with a lot of pine dust- cottonwood and algae on it.

column2: Beautiful sunny morning temp of 67 degrees with a slight breeze

column1: No wildlifel seen on or near the lake

column2: Partically cloudy warm and humid saw one little green heorn

column1: Mary + D Wayne. Balthazor helped- they will take over next year

column2: It was a partly sunny day.  Breezy
Beautiful sunny day with very little wind
We could not get the 9 foot sample to turn dark blue with the addition of Starch.  We tried 3 different samples
I did not enter any temperatures for the water since I believe that the thermometer on our Van Dorn is broke.  It only registers 59 degrees.  I will get a new Van Dorn at the start of next year.
